@startuml IMEP_Seq_Grading

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #E67E22
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FEF9E7
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #1A5276
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #5D6D7E
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam noteBorderColor #2E86C1
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EBF5FB

title IMEP — Sequence Diagram: Grade Calculation (Automated + Manual)

participant "BullMQ\nCron Worker"       as CRON
database    "MongoDB"                   as DB
actor       "Industry\nSupervisor"      as IS
actor       "Institution\nSupervisor"   as ISup
actor       Student
participant "React Frontend"            as FE
participant "Express API\n/api/industry" as API

== Automated System Score Calculation (Weekly) ==

note over CRON : Triggered by BullMQ\ngrade-calculation job

CRON -> DB   : Internship.find({ isActive: true })
DB  --> CRON : [ Internship[] ]

loop for each active student internship
  CRON -> DB   : Attendance.find({ student, internship,\ndate: { $gte: weekStart, $lte: weekEnd } })
  DB  --> CRON : [ Attendance[] ]
  CRON -> CRON : presentDays = records where\nstatus in ['present','late']
  CRON -> CRON : attendanceScore = (presentDays / totalWorkingDays) × 20\n(max 20 points)

  CRON -> DB   : LogbookWeek.findOne({ student, weekNumber })\nDailyLogEntry.countDocuments({ week })
  DB  --> CRON : { week, completedDays }
  CRON -> CRON : logbookScore = (completedDays / 5) × 30\n(max 30 points)
  CRON -> CRON : systemScore = attendanceScore + logbookScore\n(max 50 points)

  CRON -> DB   : Grade.findOneAndUpdate(\n  { student, weekNumber },\n  { attendanceScore, logbookScore, systemScore,\n    isSystemCalculated: true },\n  { upsert: true, new: true }\n)
  DB  --> CRON : Grade record saved / updated
end

== Manual Supervisor Grading ==

IS -> FE  : Navigate to Grading page
FE -> API : GET /api/industry/grading
API -> DB : Internship.findOne({ industrySupervisor })\n→ students list\n→ Grade.find({ student, internship })
DB --> API : [ { student, grades[] }[] ]
API --> FE : 200 { success, data: studentsWithGrades }
FE --> IS  : Show grading table — per student per week

IS -> FE  : Enter supervisorScore (0–50)\n+ optional note for a student/week
FE -> API : POST /api/industry/grading/:studentId/week/:weekId\n{ supervisorScore: 40, supervisorNote: "Good work" }
API -> API : protect + authorize(['industry_supervisor'])
API -> DB  : Grade.findOne({ student, logbookWeek: weekId })
DB --> API : Grade { systemScore: 38, attendanceScore: 18,\nlogbookScore: 20 }
API -> DB  : Grade.findOneAndUpdate(\n  { student, logbookWeek },\n  { supervisorScore: 40,\n    supervisorNote,\n    gradedBy: supervisorId,\n    gradedAt: now,\n    totalScore: 38 + 40 = 78 }\n)
DB --> API : Grade updated (totalScore: 78/100)
API --> FE : 200 { success, data: updatedGrade }
FE  --> IS : Grade row updates with total score

== Student Views Weekly Grade Breakdown ==

Student -> FE  : Navigate to Grades page
FE      -> API : GET /api/student/grades
API     -> DB  : Grade.find({ student: currentUser })\n.sort({ weekNumber: 1 })
DB     --> API : [ Grade[] ]
API    --> FE  : 200 { success, data: grades }
FE     --> Student : Display per-week breakdown:\n  Attendance (0–20) | Logbook (0–30)\n  Supervisor (0–50) | Total (0–100)

== Institution Supervisor Views Overview & Leaderboard ==

ISup -> FE  : Navigate to Grades Overview
FE   -> API : GET /api/institution/grades
API  -> DB  : Internship.find({ institutionSupervisor })\n→ Grade.find all for those students
DB  --> API : Aggregated grade data
API --> FE  : 200 { success, data: studentsWithGrades }
FE  --> ISup : Tabular grades overview

ISup -> FE  : Navigate to Leaderboard
FE   -> API : GET /api/institution/leaderboard
API  -> DB  : Grade.aggregate: group by student,\nsum totalScore, sort DESC
DB  --> API : Ranked student list
API --> FE  : 200 { success, data: leaderboard }
FE  --> ISup : Show ranked student list with scores

@enduml
